                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-05-24</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>The ideas behind this novel are very creative and promising however the actual story drags more than once. The last third of the book is slow and boring then rushed at the very end as if Rushdie lost interest himself. I was enraptured for the first half and yawning for the second. I'll pass on seconds.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Reader's Digest version of great books</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>3</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
